    "body": "Using git submodules is interesting, and staying close to `git submodule add` is a reasonable design decision, but if people use forge to install their dependencies it becomes a kind of package manager. The concern that I wanted to raise is about the default behavior as a package manager. I don't think the current defaults are good because it potentially installs a development version of the dependency.\r\n\r\nHow would you feel about forcing users to write a tag or branch name in the argument to `install`?",
